title: Ethereum transaction not broadcasted to the network
body:
Issue_context
There are multiple transactions made via web3j to geth. I confirmed by eth.getTransaction(hash).

The below i checked,

from eth.getTransactionReceipt(), i got null.

Even I checked in txpool.content.queued[sending_address] and txpool.content.pending[sending_address] but the return response is undefined.

I unlocked the account and initiated the transaction also, but not posted to the network.

The transaction hash has been created but it is not broadcasted to the network. The nonce is incremented by 1 for each transaction.

Its been 20 days still not broadcasted to the network. anyone, give me the suggestion.

Geth Version : 1.9.9-stable
Address : 0x0a4a6364690b5db13b7d2986b3a5b0b6dbc4d0b7
TxHash : 0x9257121829372c5d0f57b51ae760fc83c044dfe44565a2f7e41e7152dfde5ce3

If it's not in `txpool.content`, then your local node doesn't even know about it. It's a bit hard to debug something that happened 20 days ago. It won't just magically reappear in the network. Would have been nice to know the parameters, gas price, gas limits etc, as these can influence if a tx gets dropped or not.

Thanks for your reply.

If you make N transactions, they have each a unique nonce. Transaction nonces need to increase one by one, so if you send/get included tx with nonce `5`, the next transaction _must_ have nonce `6`. 

So, if your number `6` tx fails, for whatever reason, then **no** transaction with a higher nonce can __ever__ be included. What you have to do is generate a new number `6` transaction and broadcast. Only when that one has been included, can future txs go in.
